-modi-tried-but-failed-with-make-in-india-project-rahul-gandhi-in-lok-sabha-key-quotes%2Farticleshow%2F117883469.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20a%20bold%20new%20experiment%20to%20do%20away%20with%20homelessness%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Collage%20of%20a%20hotel%20and%20the%20American%20Flag.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678fe7d82fcded5e90740b87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina's%20Brentwood%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eneighborhood%2C%20standing%20out%20among%20the%20pawn%20shops%2C%20auto%20repair%20garages%2C%20and%20warehouses%20that%20dot%20the%20city's%20arterial%20Capital%20Boulevard%2C%20is%20a%20telltale%20new%20site%3A%20the%20Broadstone%20Oak%20City%20Apartments%2C%20a%20chic%20complex%20of%20muted%20earth%20tones%2C%20modern%20fonts%2C%20and%20a%20manicured%20lawn.%20The%20sprawl%20of%20one%20of%20America's%20fastest-growing%20cities%20hasn't%20quite%20reached%20Brentwood%20yet.%20But%20if%20the%20Broadstone%20and%20its%20cabana-draped%20pool%20and%20resident%20business%20center%20filled%20with%20podcasting%20gear%20is%20any%20indicator%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiami-climate-change-gentrification-flooding-housing-crisis-real-estate-prices-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egentrification%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnticipating%20the%20influx%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Raleigh%20did%20something%20unusual%3A%20It%20bought%20a%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20city%20used%20%248%20million%20in%20funds%20from%20the%20COVID-era%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-covid-plan-pandemic-schools-healthcare-vaccine-testing-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmerican%20Rescue%20Plan%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20purchase%20Hospitality%20Studios%2C%20a%20117-room%20extended-stay%20hotel%20across%20the%20street%20from%20the%20Broadstone.%20As%20the%20city%20revamps%20the%20building%2C%20the%20goal%2C%20says%20Emila%20Sutton%2C%20Raleigh's%20director%20of%20housing%20and%20neighborhoods%2C%20is%20twofold%3A%20%26quot%3Bto%20preserve%20tenancy%20for%20the%20folks%20already%20living%20there%26quot%3B%20as%20local%20rents%20are%20surely%20soon%20to%20rise%2C%20and%20to%20provide%20permanent%20housing%20for%20Raleigh's%20homeless%20population%2C%20which%20from%202021%20to%202024%20grew%20by%20200%25.%20Homelessness%20is%20surging%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeless-problem-united-states-record-unsheltered-veterans-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enationwide%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Some%20770%2C000%20people%20lived%20without%20housing%20in%20America%20in%20January%202024%2C%20120%2C000%20more%20than%20in%202023%2C%20and%20nearly%20200%2C000%20more%20than%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDue%20to%20prior%20evictions%20and%20credit%20history%2C%20many%20people%20are%20turned%20away%20from%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Sutton%20says.%20The%20hotel%2C%20which%20the%20city%20has%20renamed%20the%20Studios%20at%202800%20Brentwood%20and%20dramatically%20reduced%20room%20rates%2C%20%26quot%3Bprovides%20a%20lower-barrier-for-entry%20option%20for%20those%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20homelessness%20have%20long%20found%20refuge%20in%20nightly%20or%20weekly%20rentals%20at%20hotels%20and%20motels%2C%20that%20number%20swelled%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20often%20with%20the%20help%20of%20state%20and%20federal%20funding.%20In%20New%20York%20City%2C%209%2C000%20people%20were%20relocated%20from%20shelters%20into%20hotels.%20California's%20Project%20Roomkey%20moved%20some%2062%2C000%20people%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-simple-solution-homelessness-researcher-study-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehomelessness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20hotels%20across%20the%20state.%20For%20many%2C%20this%20was%20life-changing.%20In%20a%20study%20published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Social%20Distress%20and%20Homelessness%2C%20Deborah%20Padgett%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Silver%20School%20of%20Social%20Work%2C%20and%20two%20colleagues%20interviewed%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20formerly%20homeless%20people%20who%20stayed%20in%20hotels%20during%20stretches%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BBenefits%20of%20hotel%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bincluded%20improvement%20in%20physical%20health%2C%20sleep%2C%20personal%20hygiene%2C%20privacy%2C%20safety%2C%20nutrition%2C%20and%20overall%20well-being.%26quot%3B%20They%20concluded%20that%20%26quot%3Ban%20unprecedented%20opportunity%20has%20arisen%20from%20the%20pandemic%20to%20end%20homelessness%20for%20many.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaleigh%20joins%20several%20cities%20across%20the%20country%20attempting%20to%20make%20hotels%20a%20more%20permanent%20housing%20solution.%20In%20October%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Chicago%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epurchased%20the%20historic%20Diplomat%20Motel%2C%20rechristening%20it%20Haven%20on%20Lincoln%2C%20which%20provides%20people%20experiencing%20homelessness%20with%20access%20to%20their%20own%20rooms.%20In%20Brooklyn's%20ultraexpensive%20Dumbo%20neighborhood%2C%20the%20recently%20renovated%2090%20Sands%20will%20provide%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loves-gym-weightlifting-workout-fitness-trends-planet-fitness-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egym%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20computer%20lab%2C%20and%20bicycle%20storage%20%E2%80%94%20to%20hundreds%20of%20people%20who%20had%20been%20living%20on%20the%20streets.%20In%20early%202024%2C%20Rep.%20Suzanne%20Bonamici%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Oregon%2C%20introduced%20the%20%26quot%3BProject%20Turnkey%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20if%20passed%20would%20provide%20%241%20billion%20annually%2C%20via%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%2C%20to%20purchase%20and%20convert%20unused%20hotels%2C%20schools%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20office%20buildings%20across%20the%20country%20into%20housing%20or%20to%20add%20to%20shelter%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20people%20without%20homes%20is%20not%20purely%20altruistic%2C%20Sutton%20adds.%20She%20notes%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fendhomelessness.org%2Fresource%2Fending-chronic-homelessness-saves-taxpayers-money-2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%202017%20study%20by%20the%20National%20Alliance%20to%20End%20Homelessness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20the%20taxpayer%20cost%20of%20supporting%20homelessness%20(for%20public%20services%20from%20shelters%20to%20hospitals)%20can%20range%20anywhere%20from%20%2435%2C000%20to%20%2496%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20per%20person.%20If%20those%20people%20are%20housed%2C%20that%20cost%20drops%20to%20between%20%2418%2C000%20and%20%2434%2C000.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20affordable%20to%20house%20people%2C%20overall%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sutton.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20most%20of%20these%20people%20just%20need%20light-touch%20support%2C%20such%20as%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Raleigh's%20and%20the%20country's%20other%20hotels-to-housing%20projects%20remain%20nascent%2C%20and%20face%20many%20hurdles%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20has%20been%20on%20board%20with%20the%20hotel-to-housing%20concept.%20Because%20they%20take%20away%20cities'%20hotel%20inventory%2C%20nightly%20rates%20at%20hotels%20around%20them%20can%20increase.%20Last%20May%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20that%20one%20in%20five%20of%20New%20York%20City's%20hotels%20had%20entered%20a%20migrant%20shelter%20program%2C%20leading%20rates%20to%20jump%20sharply.%20(Some%20of%20that%20increase%20is%20also%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-numbers-shrink-hotel-prices-soar-ban-nyc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20city's%20crackdown%20on%20Airbnb%20properties%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20with%20general%20global%20inflation.)%20In%20contentious%20town%20meetings%20where%20hotel%20conversions%20have%20been%20proposed%2C%20residents%20have%20also%20shared%20fears%20that%20they'd%20make%20their%20neighborhoods%20more%20susceptible%20to%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cities%2C%20especially%20New%20York%2C%20hotel%20housing%20projects%20have%20faced%20significant%20opposition%20from%20hotel%20unions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20prohibitive%20remodeling%20expenses%20necessary%20to%20meet%20local%20zoning%20regulations%20and%20building%20codes%2C%20which%20are%20often%20stricter%20for%20affordable%20housing%20than%20they%20are%20for%20hotels.%20Some%20hotel%20elevators%20and%20doorways%2C%20for%20example%2C%20are%20smaller%20and%20shorter%20than%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-homebuyers-mortgage-rates-spring-real-estate-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresidential%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%2C%20and%20additional%20requirements%20that%20each%20unit%20have%20a%20full-size%20fridge%2C%20stovetop%2C%20and%20sink%20can%20be%20particularly%20pricey.%20In%20a%202022%20Politico%20article%2C%20one%20New%20York%20architect%20called%20the%20city's%20stringent%20conversion%20legislation%20a%20%26quot%3Bclassic%20case%20of%20the%20perfect%20being%20the%20enemy%20of%20the%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Raleigh%2C%20however%2C%20there%20hasn't%20yet%20been%20any%20noticeable%20pushback%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-global-dominance-brazil-china-japan-chesky-cities-regulation-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehotel%20project%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20Sutton.%20For%20one%2C%20the%20Brentwood%20neighborhood%20is%20still%20a%20ways%20off%20from%20feeling%20the%20effects%20of%20Raleigh's%20sprawl.%20The%20city%20also%20decided%20to%20circumvent%20regulatory%20rigmarole%20by%20keeping%20the%20building%20zoned%20as%20a%20hotel.%20That%20said%2C%20getting%20the%20building%20ready%20has%20been%20a%20yearslong%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Studios%20at%202800%20looks%20every%20bit%20the%20typical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fluxury-real-estate-condos-miami-branded-residences-porsche-lamborghini-homebuyers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextended-stay%20hotel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20banks%20of%20rooms%20running%20along%20an%20exterior%20sidewalk%20on%20the%20first%20floor%20and%20an%20elevated%20walkway%20on%20the%20second%2C%20a%20cluster%20of%20oak%20trees%20out%20back%2C%20and%20a%20filled-in%20pool%20sitting%20among%20tangled%20weeds%20and%20cracked%20concrete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20purchasing%20the%20property%2C%20the%20city%20received%20a%20%2415%20million%20quote%20from%20a%20local%20architect%20for%20a%20complete%20renovation.%20Given%20the%20steep%20cost%2C%20Raleigh%20took%20something%20of%20a%20triage%20approach%20in%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20move%20people%20in%20more%20expediently.%20After%20reviewing%20four%20bids%20for%20a%20property%20manager%2C%20Raleigh%20chose%20CASA%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20nonprofit%20that%20specializes%20in%20providing%20stable%20and%20affordable%20housing%20for%20the%20homeless%20across%20North%20Carolina's%20Research%20Triangle%20region.%20Together%2C%20the%20city%20and%20CASA%20decided%20to%20first%20update%20the%20fire%20alarms%20and%20sprinklers%2C%20add%20a%20new%20WiFi%20system%2C%20and%20rebuild%20some%20of%20the%20hotel's%20crumbling%20exterior%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-stair-apartments-condos-housing-crisis-solution-rent-home-prices-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estaircases%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20then%2C%20CASA%20has%20been%20rehabbing%20rooms%20as%20they%20become%20available%2C%20moving%20existing%20residents%20into%20recently%20finished%20rooms%20in%20order%20to%20tackle%20the%20outdated%20ones.%20Currently%2C%2070%20units%20are%20operational%2C%20all%20of%20which%20were%20occupied%20when%20I%20recently%20spoke%20with%20CASA's%20CEO%20Everett%20McElveen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20that%20we%20don't%20displace%20anyone%20while%20we%20renovate%2C%20which%20is%20why%20we%20have%20to%20do%20it%20in%20phases%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20before%20I%20spoke%20with%20McElveen%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eemployees%20from%20Sutton's%20office%20filled%20six%20rooms%20with%20people%20who%20were%20previously%20living%20in%20encampments%20scattered%20in%20and%20around%20Raleigh.%20Erika%20Brandt%2C%20Raleigh's%20assistant%20director%20of%20housing%20and%20neighborhoods%20department%2C%20said%20those%20rooms%20were%20filled%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20participants%20in%20Bringing%20Neighbors%20Home%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%245%20million%20two-year%20pilot%20program%20aimed%20at%20mitigating%20homelessess%20that%20the%20city%20launched%20in%20the%20fall%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20few%20folks%20who%20are%20not%20part%20of%20the%20pilot%20but%20who%20were%20referred%20to%20the%20Studios%20due%20to%20extreme%20medical%20vulnerability%20making%20it%20high%20priority%20to%20move%20them%20indoors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20rooms%20were%20given%20what%20McElveen%20calls%20%26quot%3Blight%20facelifts%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fresh%20paint%20job%20and%20new%20furniture%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bso%20it%20feels%20more%20like%20an%20apartment%20than%20a%20hotel%20room.%26quot%3B%20Once%20a%20new%20bank%20of%20rooms%20is%20ready%2C%20McElveen%20says%2C%20the%20residents%20in%20the%20facelifted%20rooms%20will%20be%20moved%20and%20those%20areas%20will%20be%20gutted%20for%20more%20thorough%20renovations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20and%20CASA%20plan%20to%20convert%20a%20small%20number%20of%20the%20building's%20suites%20into%20conference%20rooms%20within%20the%20next%20few%20years%20to%20provide%20on-site%20support%20services%20and%20office%20spaces%20for%20CASA's%20behavioral%20health%20intervention%20team%20to%20work%20with%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECASA%20also%20plans%20to%20turn%20the%20hotel's%20filled-in%20pool%20into%20a%20common%20area%2C%20with%20grills%2C%20green%20grass%2C%20chairs%2C%20and%20benches%20for%20residents%20to%20relax%20and%20socialize%2C%20and%20to%20convert%20the%20entire%20building%20to%20solar%20power%20to%20lower%20utility%20costs.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAll%20these%20updates%20require%20additional%20funding%2C%20and%20Sutton's%20office%20has%20been%20submitting%20a%20capital%20improvement%20plan%20request%20to%20the%20city%20to%20continue%20to%20support%20the%20estimated%20%2411%20million%20in%20remaining%20improvements%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20building%20remains%20a%20hotel%2C%20to%20book%20a%20room%2C%20prospective%20tenants%20can%20simply%20call%20or%20visit%20the%20front%20desk.%20A%20room%20at%20Hospitality%20Studios%20could%20cost%20as%20much%20as%20%24379%20a%20week.%20For%20now%2C%20most%20rooms%20go%20for%20%24200%20a%20week.%20Though%20there's%20no%20work%20requirement%20to%20get%20a%20room%2C%20tenants%20who%20are%20employed%20can%20get%20a%20lower%20rate%20if%20they%20provide%20income%20documentation%20to%20the%20city%2C%20which%20ensures%20that%20no%20one%20pays%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20for%20rent.%20If%20there's%20no%20vacancy%2C%20the%20city%20will%20work%20with%20people%20to%20help%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-losing-big-advantage-college-workers-wages-housing-costs-salaries-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efind%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELynnette%20Moore%20is%20the%20hotel's%20longest-tenured%20resident.%20In%20her%2017%20years%20there%2C%20she's%20seen%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%2C%20of%20people%20come%20and%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20mostly%20stay%20to%20themselves.%20It's%20quiet.%20People%20are%20just%20trying%20to%20live%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20recent%20changes%20have%20begun%20to%20foster%20more%20of%20a%20sense%20of%20community.%20%26quot%3BNow%20people%20seem%20to%20talk%20a%20bit%20more.%20Maybe%20when%20that%20area%20is%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20planned%20common%20space%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe'll%20all%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECASA%20hopes%20to%20have%20the%20Studios%20at%202800%20fully%20renovated%20by%202030.%20By%20then%2C%20Raleigh's%20sprawl%20will%20have%20likely%20swallowed%20up%20the%20Brentwood%20neighborhood%2C%20transforming%20it%20into%20something%20wholly%20unrecognizable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Venutolo-Mantovani%20has%20written%20for%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20National%20Geographic%2C%20Cond%C3%A9%20Nast%20Traveler%2C%20Wired%2C%20and%20many%20others.%20He%20lives%20in%20Chapel%20Hill%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20their%20two%20children.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbold-new-experiment-homelessness-hotels-housing-crisis-rent-inflation-raleigh-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738573682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678fe7a810c98eace9133cd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider