0low-income%20older%20Americans%20struggle%20to%20navigate%20benefit%20thresholds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-medicaid-snap-benefits-income-reliance-increases-aging-population-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceiving%20government%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20increased%20over%20the%20past%20several%20decades.%20Programs%20like%20Medicaid%2C%20SNAP%2C%20and%20Social%20Security%20made%20up%2018%25%20of%20total%20personal%20income%20in%20the%20US%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20totaling%20%243.8%20trillion%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20a%209%20percentage-point%20increase%20from%201970%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fgreat-transfermation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20a%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20September%202024%20by%20the%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group.%20The%20report%20said%20that%20the%20aging%20US%20population%20and%20skyrocketing%20healthcare%20costs%20are%20the%20main%20reasons%20for%20the%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoverty-line-leaves-behind-low-income-americans-snap-medicare-wic-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20poverty%20line%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20remained%20largely%20unchanged%20since%20the%201960s.%20The%20threshold%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20%2415%2C650%20annually%20for%20one%20person%2C%20is%20adjusted%20each%20year%20for%20inflation%20but%20does%20not%20account%20for%20local%20cost%20of%20living%20or%20changing%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQualification%20standards%20for%20safety%20nets%20like%20SNAP%20and%20Medicaid%20are%20largely%20based%20on%20this%20measure%20%E2%80%94%20Americans%20making%20up%20to%20133%25%20of%20the%20poverty%20line%20can%20receive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicaid.gov%2Fmedicaid%2Feligibility-policy%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%