me%20would%20reduce%20her%20SNAP%20benefit%20and%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20buy%20enough%20groceries%20for%20her%20household.%20She%20added%20that%20her%20monthly%20SNAP%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fsnap%2Fchanges-2023-benefit-amounts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20reduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month%20because%20of%20the%20annual%20Social%20Security%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fcola%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost-of-living%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20received%2C%20and%20her%20household%20is%20a%20few%20months%20behind%20on%20bills%20because%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20lost%20his%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20no%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20scary%20as%20hell%20for%20people%20to%20not%20be%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20their%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Shaw%2C%20director%20of%20the%20benefits%20transformation%20initiative%20at%20the%20Aspen%20Institute%20and%20the%20senior%20policy%20advisor%20for%20the%20Aspen%20Financial%20Security%20Program%2C%20said%20that%20benefit%20qualification%20thresholds%20can%20be%20stressful%20to%20navigate%2C%20especially%20for%20older%20adults%20reentering%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOften%20eligibility%20for%20different%20programs%20like%20SNAP%2C%20Medicaid%2C%20SSI%2C%20housing%2C%20they're%20not%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20household%20qualifies%20for%20multiple%20benefits%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20track%20the%20income%20limits%20of%20several%20programs%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20which%20can%20get%20really%20confusing%20and%20cause%20people%20to%20not%20take%20that%20new%20job%20or%20not%20take%20that%20raise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaw%20added%20that%20some%20safety%20net%20programs%2C%20like%20SSI%2C%20which%20provides%20benefits%20to%20disabled%20Americans%2C%20have%20asset%20limits.%20People%20receiving%20SSI%20can't%20hold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fssi%2Fspotlights%2Fspot-resources.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSupplemental%2520Security%2520Income%2520(SSI)%2520is%2Ccount%2520toward%2520the%2520resource%2520limit.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20%242%2C000%20in%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20value%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20cars%2C%20and%20savings%20accounts%20%E2%80%94%20without%20disrupting%20their%20benefits.%20Other%20programs%2C%20like%20SNAP%2C%20have%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fsnap%2Fwork-requirements%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20requirements%20and%20income%20caps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20leaves%20beneficiaries%20walking%20a%20tightrope%20with%20how%20much%20they%20can%20earn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e006aab-ba1a-4cb2-895e-b9520c049522%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20back%20to%20work%20helps%20some%20retirees%20boost%20their%20income%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20trade-off%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20some%20low-income%20older%20Americans%20like%20Rufino%20and%20Murray%20feel%20caught%20in%20a%20benefits%20catch-22%2C%20others%20find%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareers-regrets-retirement-unemployment-boomers-college-degree-age-discrimination-ageism-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturning%20to%20the%20labor%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20in%20their%20best%20financial%20interest.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-regrets-saving-investing-loneliness-parenting-older-americans-survey-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20has%20heard%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20older%20adults%20who%20chose%20to%20work%20beyond%20retirement%20age%20or%20'unretire'%20during%20their%20golden%20years%20as%20a%20way%20to%20stay%20active%20or%20supplement%20their%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20Security%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fpubs%2FEN-05-10069.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ere