%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Can%20Bangladesh-Pakistan%20Warming%20Be%20A%20Threat%20To%20South%20Asia%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20geopolitical%20landscape%20of%20South%20Asia%20is%20currently%20abuzz%20with%20discussions%20on%20the%20renewed%20warmth%20in%20Pakistan%E2%80%93Bangladesh%20relations.%20In%20India%E2%80%94and%20consequently%2C%20much%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%94the%20perception%20of%20this%20relationship%20is%20deeply%20shaped%20by%20historical%20events%2C%20particularly%20those%20of%20March%201971%2C%20when%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20launched%20genocidal%20attacks%20on%20intellectuals%20at%20Dhaka%20University%20and%20others%20who%20championed%20the%20cause%20of%20Bangladeshi%20independence.%20The%20images%20of%20December%201971%2C%20culminating%20in%20Pakistan's%20surrender%20and%20the%20triumphant%20return%20of%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%20to%20Dhaka%20in%20January%201972%2C%20further%20reinforce%20this%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOld%20Assumptions%20Die%20Hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20historical%20narratives%2C%20a%20long-standing%20assumption%20has%20taken%20root%20in%20the%20Indian%20psyche%20that%20after%20Pakistan's%20division%20into%20two%20nations%20and%20its%20decisive%20military%20defeat%E2%80%94marked%20by%20the%20surrender%20of%2093%2C000%20prisoners%20of%20war%E2%80%94it%20no%20longer%20posed%20a%20significant%20military%20threat%20to%20India.%20Another%20widely%20held%20belief%20is%20that%20Bangladesh%2C%20owing%20its%20birth%20as%20a%20nation%20to%20India's%20intervention%20and%20sacrifices%20in%20the%201971%20Indo-Pak%20War%2C%20would%20remain%20perpetually%20grateful%20and%20maintain%20strong%20ties%20with%20India.%20While%20Indo-Bangladesh%20relations%20have%20remained%20largely%20positive%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20certain%20factors%E2%80%94such%20as%20the%20assassination%20of%20Sheikh%20Mujib%20in%201975%2C%20the%20sheltering%20of%20separatist%20leaders%20from%20India's%20Northeast%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20and%20the%20persistent%20issue%20of%20illegal%20migration%E2%80%94have%20occasionally%20strained%20perceptions.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20Bangladesh%20realigning%20with%20Pakistan%20after%2054%20years%20remains%20inconceivable%20to%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20these%20five%20decades%2C%20India%20has%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20Bangladesh's%20economic%20growth%20through%20trade%2C%20investment%2C%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20energy%20cooperation%2C%20technical%20training%2C%20financial%20aid%2C%20and%20policy%20support.%20These%20contributions%20have%20significantly%20enhanced%20Bangladesh's%20economic%20capabilities%20and%20global%20standing.%20However%2C%20does%20a%20regime%20change%20in%20Dhaka%20now%20position%20India%20as%20an%20adversary%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20Bangladesh's%20leadership%3F%20The%20brutal%20history%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20Army's%20actions%20in%201971%E2%80%94rape%2C%20torture%2C%20and%20genocide%E2%80%94seems%20to%20have%20faded%20from%20collective%20memory.%20The%20recent%20high-profile%20visits%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20appear%20to%20challenge%20the%20longstanding%20Indo-Bangladesh%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Goings-On%20In%20Chittagong%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20notable%20visits%20was%20that%20of%20a%20six-member%20high-level%20delegation%20from%20the%20Bangladesh%20Army%20to%20Rawalpindi%2C%20led%20by%20Lt%20Gen%20Kamrul%20Zaman%2C%20Principal%20Staff%20Officer%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20Armed%20Forces%20Division%E2%80%94effectively%20the%20second-in-command%20after%20the%20Chief.%20Shortly%20thereafter%2C%20Pakistan's%20ISI%20Director%20General%20of%20Analysis%2C%20Maj%20Gen%20Shahid%20Amir%20Afsar%2C%20along%20with%20other%20senior%20officials%2C%20visited%20Dhaka.%20Unconfirmed%20reports%20suggest%20that%20this%20delegation%20travelled%20to%20Rangpur%2C%20a%20cantonment%20near%20the%20Siliguri%20Corridor%E2%80%94an%20area%20often%20perceived%20as%20India's%20Achilles'%20heel%2C%20though%20perhaps%20not%20as%20vulnerable%20as%20it%20is%20made%20out%20to%20be.%20The%20delegation%20also%20visited%20Chittagong%20and%20held%20meetings%20with%20tribal%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fundamental%20truth%20in%20international%20relations%20is%20that%20a%20change%20in%20regime%20does%20not%20automatically%20render%20the%20people%20of%20one%20nation%20hostile%20to%20another.%20However%2C%20the%20new%20Bangladesh%20government%E2%80%94questionably%20constituted%20as%20it%20is%E2%80%94seems%20intent%20on%20shifting%20the%20subcontinental%20balance.%20The%20hastily%20arranged%20exchanges%20between%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20particularly%20the%20visits%20to%20Rangpur%20and%20beyond%2C%20signal%20a%20potential%20realignment%20that%20India%20cannot%20afford%20to%20ignore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChittagong%20presents%20an%20obvious%20signal%20to%20any%20observer%20that%20the%20military%20establishment%20is%20attempting%20to%20highlight%20India's%20perceived%20vulnerabilities%E2%80%94suggesting%20that%20these%20vulnerabilities%20are%20jointly%20in%20the%20crosshairs%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh.%20However%2C%20no%20serious%20military%20strategist%20would%20interpret%20this%20as%20a%20direct%20threat%3B%20a%20mere%20high-level%20visit%20does%20not%20constitute%20one.%20Instead%2C%20what%20the%20Pakistan-Bangladesh%20duo%20is%20attempting%20is%20to%20send%20a%20message%E2%80%94perhaps%20several.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMessages%20To%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20they%20aim%20to%20indicate%20that%20peace%20and%20stability%20along%20the%20Bangladesh%20border%20cannot%20be%20taken%20for%20granted%20while%20India%20is%20focused%20on%20securing%20its%20western%20front.%20Second%2C%20they%20seek%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20both%20nations%20and%20their%20militaries%20are%20willing%20to%20set%20aside%20their%20turbulent%20past%20and%20cooperate%20against%20perceived%20common%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20now%2C%20one%20reassuring%20factor%20in%20Bangladesh%20has%20been%20that%20the%20Bangladesh%20Army%20remained%20only%20partially%20influenced%20by%20political%20turmoil%20and%20street-level%20unrest.%20That%20it%20has%20now%20been%20increasingly%20swayed%20by%20the%20growing%20anti-India%20sentiment%20in%20Bangladesh%20is%20not%20entirely%20surprising.%20Notably%2C%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20safe%20evacuation%20to%20India%20occurred%20with%20the%20Army's%20support.%20So%20far%2C%20there%20had%20been%20little%20evidence%20of%20a%20shift%20in%20its%20outlook%2C%20though%20some%20signs%20may%20have%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20The%20Pragmatists%20Speak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPersonally%2C%20I%20have%20always%20held%20a%20positive%20view%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20Army.%20Its%20senior%20leadership%20had%20the%20intellectual%20bandwidth%20to%20engage%20with%20me%20for%20an%20hour%20on%20my%20perspectives%20regarding%20political%20Islam%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20balanced%20approach.%20In%20professional%20interactions%E2%80%94particularly%20within%20UN%20peacekeeping%20operations%E2%80%94Bangladesh%20Army%20officers%20have%20consistently%20demonstrated%20a%20mature%20and%20pragmatic%20approach%20to%20faith.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20has%20been%20the%20Bangladesh%20Army%20that%20has%20served%20as%20a%20buffer%2C%20preventing%20Bangladesh%20from%20succumbing%20entirely%20to%20Islamist%20radicalisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20do%20well%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%2C%20which%20is%20now%20grappling%20with%20the%20consequences%20of%20fostering%20radicalism%20and%20terrorism%E2%80%94finding%20it%20impossible%20to%20dismount%20the%20proverbial%20tiger.%20Fortunately%2C%20there%20are%20still%20enough%20pragmatists%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20both%20in%20and%20out%20of%20uniform%2C%20who%20understand%20the%20risks%20of%20aligning%20too%20closely%20with%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrumpian%20Concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Trump%202.0%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20amused%20by%20the%20reckless%20policies%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%20that%20facilitated%20Mohammad%20Yunus's%20rise%20to%20power%E2%80%94along%20with%20a%20government%20that%20shows%20little%20regard%20for%20its%20minority%20communities.%20Given%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20faltering%20and%20manufacturing%20is%20at%20its%20lowest%20in%20years%2C%20Trump%20has%20the%20leverage%20to%20reverse%20the%20situation%20with%20strategic%20aid%20manipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20with%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20Jaishankar%20already%20engaged%20with%20the%20new%20U.S.%20administration%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20expected%20to%20meet%20President%20Trump%20in%20February%202025%2C%20a%20favourable%20outcome%20seems%20likely.%20Trump%20has%20little%20tolerance%20for%20those%20seeking%20to%20create%20instability%20where%20none%20exists.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIndia%2C%20on%20its%20part%2C%20remains%20unfazed%20by%20recent%20developments%2C%20maintaining%20its%20strategy%20of%20quiet%20diplomacy%20over%20rhetoric%E2%80%94an%20approach%20that%20continues%20to%20be%20its%20best%20bet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20writer%20is%20a%20Member%20of%20the%20National%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%2C%20Chancellor%20of%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Former%20GOC%20of%20the%20Srinagar-based%2015%20Corps.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738568040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fusgt349o_pakistan_625x300_03_February_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbangladesh-must-understand-the-risks-of-getting-too-close-to-pakistan-7622340%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20would%20do%20well%20